The sol-gel method was employed to synthesize Mg–ZnFe2O4. A 0.5 M aqueous solution of Mg(NO3)2∙6H2O and a 0.5 M aqueous solution of Zn(NO3)2∙6H2O were combined with a 2 M aqueous solution of Fe(NO3)3∙9H2O while stirring constantly. The chelating agent (
C ₆ H ₈ O ₇
) was introduced in the above solution after 30 min of stirring. The solution was then kept at 90 °C with steady stirring for ∼5 h. A crimson gel was obtained which was subsequently dried at 150 °C. Finally, Mg–ZnFe2O4 was acquired by the calcination of the above product at 1000 °C in a muffle furnace for 4 h.

